00:46.256 --> 00:50.642
If you go into my office over there, you'll see that that library has been built around theology.

00:51.483 --> 00:56.009
But then it got to the point where it's like, I want to experience you beyond just cerebral.

00:56.029 --> 01:02.418
Not that that he bypasses our mind, but then he wants us to have these moments with him, these encounters with him.

01:02.722 --> 01:10.113
And so we've been in Psalm 23, which is probably one of the most famous of all sections of scripture, other than John 3 16, right?

01:10.133 --> 01:12.116
You ever seen that guy with the big sign at NFL games?

01:12.156 --> 01:12.416
Boom.

01:13.138 --> 01:18.766
So that's a very popular verse, but I'm talking about a section of scripture that is very well known, Psalm 23.

01:19.347 --> 01:22.031
We need to experience it regularly.

01:22.391 --> 01:26.978
And to experience as I prayed, God as shepherd, we need to trust Him.

01:26.998 --> 01:27.259
Amen?

01:28.160 --> 01:29.983
You gotta trust God and keep trusting Him.

01:30.523 --> 01:32.306
That's what we looked at last Lord's day.

01:32.642 --> 01:36.549
Now we're going to talk about humility or humbling ourselves.

01:36.929 --> 01:38.091
So let me ask you a question.

01:38.211 --> 01:39.133
Are you a humble person?

01:39.153 --> 01:43.039
Raise your hand.

01:43.059 --> 01:43.640
Trick question.

01:45.604 --> 01:46.766
Oh, I don't mean to put you on the spot.

01:47.827 --> 01:48.849
What is humility?

01:49.670 --> 01:51.153
What is humility?

01:52.195 --> 01:56.562
Someone once said it's not thinking less of yourself, but thinking of yourself less.

01:58.722 --> 02:00.284
Some of my heroes are the Puritans.

02:00.324 --> 02:01.025
I've quoted some.

02:01.045 --> 02:01.866
I'm gonna quote one now.

02:01.966 --> 02:07.314
Thomas Watson said, a humble soul is emptied of all swelling thoughts of himself.

02:08.576 --> 02:10.178
You ever had swelling thoughts of yourself?

02:11.500 --> 02:13.542
That's an interesting way to put it, isn't it?

02:15.665 --> 02:16.366
What is humility?

02:16.386 --> 02:18.209
I know humility is hard to hold on to.

02:18.469 --> 02:21.313
I know for me, I've asked the Lord many years ago, make me a humble person.

02:21.914 --> 02:23.156
Oh boy, that's a scary prayer.

02:23.216 --> 02:24.978
It's like asking the Lord for patience, right?

02:26.050 --> 02:28.733
Ask the Lord for humility and watch what happens in your life.

02:28.793 --> 02:31.856
And so I started buying book after book after book after book on humility.

02:32.577 --> 02:35.660
And so humility to me is like the watermelon that used to have seeds.

02:35.700 --> 02:36.761
Remember those watermelons?

02:37.161 --> 02:38.283
Now it's like no more seeds.

02:38.303 --> 02:39.164
What happened to all the seeds?

02:39.684 --> 02:42.007
