02:42.127 --> 02:47.352
My parents would say after I got done spitting out all the seeds on the ground or the floor to pick up all the seeds.

02:47.392 --> 02:50.135
And so I try to pick it up and what would happen when I grab it with my fingers?

02:50.235 --> 02:53.138
It would whip, it would whip, you know, it just kind of slips out.

02:53.218 --> 02:54.359
That's the way humility is.

02:54.439 --> 03:00.065
Sometimes we're going to think that we're humble, that we have it, we have a grasp on humility, but we know them because before you know it, it's gone.

03:01.146 --> 03:02.687
And then the swelling thoughts come back, right?

03:04.209 --> 03:05.850
And so we're going to talk about humility.

03:05.870 --> 03:07.272
What's the opposite of humility?

03:07.312 --> 03:07.632
Everybody?

03:07.732 --> 03:08.073
What is it?

03:09.234 --> 03:09.614
Pride.

03:10.355 --> 03:10.615
