It was rough.

29:11.949 --> 29:14.533
And so I said to the law, I said, Lord, what am I going to get out of all of this?

29:14.613 --> 29:15.574
Why am I going through this?

29:15.614 --> 29:16.695
Why are Lisa and I going through?

29:16.715 --> 29:19.058
It wasn't a marital thing, our marriage was strong, so it was beyond that.

29:19.459 --> 29:24.005
I don't want you to think that the marriage thing was being under attack, although it has been under attack through the years, but this wasn't it.

29:25.206 --> 29:28.210
And so I'm praying to the Lord, and I said, Lord, what am I going to get out of this?

29:29.218 --> 29:30.119
And he said, you're going to get me.

29:30.159 --> 29:33.502
That's what you're going to get.

29:33.522 --> 29:34.283
And I'm just balling.

29:35.725 --> 29:36.205
You're enough.

29:36.305 --> 29:37.006
You're sufficient.

29:37.046 --> 29:38.547
Remember, we're talking about sufficiency here.

29:39.528 --> 29:40.469
The Lord is my shepherd.

29:40.589 --> 29:41.891
I shall not want.

29:43.152 --> 29:49.518
And so if I'm wanting the world or if I'm wanting all these other things and not Jesus Christ himself, then I'm not in a good spot.

29:49.538 --> 29:50.179
And that's pride.

29:51.140 --> 29:52.201
That's all that connects to.

29:53.182 --> 29:55.765
And so here's the teaching here.

29:55.825 --> 29:57.106
Jesus is saying deny.

29:57.762 --> 30:00.005
deny, not forget yourself, but deny yourself.

30:00.105 --> 30:05.673
And I remember during that season of my life writing in my journal, Lord, I feel like I have to die a thousand deaths.

30:07.095 --> 30:07.916
I still keep my journals.

30:07.936 --> 30:10.499
I looked at them the other day, 30 years of keeping a journal.

30:11.060 --> 30:12.282
So I have lots of them.

30:12.502 --> 30:21.534
And so I go back through those and you'll see in those journals that I say, I don't want to die today, like to myself, not physically or anything like that.

30:21.554 --> 30:22.355
I don't want to alarm anybody.

30:22.976 --> 30:24.338
We've got some young people in the room.

30:24.482 --> 30:26.304
It's not that, it's denying myself.

30:26.364 --> 30:28.346
I had to deny and die to myself.

30:29.187 --> 30:30.188
That's a pride issue.

30:31.670 --> 30:33.332
And so I said, well, I don't want to do that anymore.

30:34.333 --> 30:34.993
And what do you say to me?

30:35.574 --> 30:35.854
Do you know?

30:37.036 --> 30:38.217
Okay, you don't have to die anymore.

30:39.638 --> 30:40.159
Is that what he said?

30:41.400 --> 30:42.662
No, he's going, you have to keep doing this.

30:43.503 --> 30:52.052
As long as you're in this body, this flesh, because my flesh wants to take the provision of God and consume it upon my flesh, my fallenness.

30:52.773 --> 30:54.034
We don't want that, that's pride.

30:55.394 --> 30:59.660
Verse 26, he said, what would it profit a man if he gains the whole world and loses his soul?

31:00.181 --> 31:07.411
So in conclusion, for us to experientially say that the Lord is my shepherd, we'll have to trust the shepherd.

31:07.871 --> 31:08.392
Trust him.

31:08.813 --> 31:12.037
Keep trusting him and keep humbling yourself before him.

31:12.638 --> 31:13.339
Make the choice.

31:13.760 --> 31:15.582
You know humility is a choice.

31:16.003 --> 31:16.543
Did you know that?

31:18.526 --> 31:21.150
We can either choose to be prideful or humble.

31:22.612 --> 31:24.114
And I want to choose humility.

31:24.962 --> 31:25.983
Do you want to choose humility?

31:27.185 --> 31:27.465
Amen?

31:29.748 --> 31:30.750
Uh-oh.

31:30.770 --> 31:32.532
There wasn't too many hands that went up on that one.

31:32.993 --> 31:34.314
That should be 100%, right?

31:34.334 --> 31:35.937
It should be 100%.

31:36.317 --> 31:38.079
There's something I want to show you.

31:38.099 --> 31:40.543
It's called the triangle of sufficiency, and I'll bring it to a close.

31:40.623 --> 31:41.464
It's wonderful.

31:41.905 --> 31:44.648
You start with trust or faith, and then it goes to humility.

31:45.349 --> 31:50.095
This place of denying yourself as we looked at Jesus saying here to them, and then it moves over to love.

31:50.156 --> 31:52.018
And we'll talk about love in a couple of weeks.

31:52.322 --> 31:54.164
together, the triangle of sufficiency.

31:54.204 --> 31:56.766
How do we have a sufficient relationship with God?

31:57.327 --> 32:03.793
How is Jesus really the shepherd of our life in a total and complete perfect sense of the word?

32:04.233 --> 32:05.174
You need faith.

32:06.035 --> 32:06.836
You need trusting.

32:06.856 --> 32:07.817
That's the word I'll use there.

32:08.277 --> 32:09.238
And then humility.

32:09.518 --> 32:12.781
Both of those are necessary and important.

32:13.142 --> 32:14.183
So I'm gonna ask you a question.

32:14.203 --> 32:17.346
Do you trust him and are you humbling yourself before him?

32:17.686 --> 32:20.689
This is what Dave Ripper said and I love it.

32:20.809 --> 32:21.970
It's a great quote

32:22.466 --> 32:26.551
Our lead pastor said, greater trust leads to greater humility.

32:26.611 --> 32:28.733
Greater humility leads to greater love.

32:29.394 --> 32:32.577
Greater love leads to greater trust, and it just keeps going.

32:33.658 --> 32:34.179
It's so good.

32:34.840 --> 32:38.484
Let's just keep doing these things, and you'll see the sufficiency of the shepherd.

32:39.245 --> 32:41.107
And we can say, the Lord is my shepherd.

32:41.127 --> 32:43.930
I shall not want.

32:44.410 --> 32:45.451
The Lord hates pride.

32:45.812 --> 32:51.378
Psalm 23, I'm sorry, Psalm 73, verse 6 says, pride is their necklace.

32:52.034 --> 32:53.055
I'm not a big jewelry guy.

32:53.536 --> 32:54.597
I don't wear necklaces.

32:54.938 --> 32:56.220
I usually wear a watch.

32:56.240 --> 32:58.182
I don't wear necklaces, but this is interesting.

32:58.643 --> 33:02.568
And so these people, prideful people, it's like they want to show off their bling bling.

33:03.870 --> 33:06.173
You don't want to show off pride as the bling bling.

33:07.335 --> 33:09.077
And so this is what the psalmist said.

33:09.538 --> 33:12.622
Proverbs 29, 23 says, one's pride will bring him low.

33:13.303 --> 33:17.689
The prophet Isaiah 2, 11 said, the lofty pride of man shall be brought low.

33:17.769 --> 33:18.770
Humble yourselves.

33:19.042 --> 33:21.925
I think it was James that said, just humble yourself before the Lord and he'll lift you up.

33:21.945 --> 33:24.287
It might have been Peter, I'm sorry if I got that wrong.

33:24.727 --> 33:28.711
I think both of them talked about humility and so trusting.

33:28.731 --> 33:29.992
Okay, here's the application test.

33:30.052 --> 33:30.413
Are you ready?

33:31.354 --> 33:32.154
You'll see it on the screen.

33:32.735 --> 33:34.417
Application test, how often do you pray?

33:35.878 --> 33:36.378
How often?

33:37.660 --> 33:40.903
And so if you're praying without ceasing, you're probably trusting without ceasing.

33:40.923 --> 33:44.706
Paul said trust without or constantly pray without ceasing, pardon me.

33:45.427 --> 33:48.530
So if you're trusting the Lord, are you praying a whole lot?

33:48.962 --> 33:49.623
Do they go together?

33:50.444 --> 33:50.664
Yeah.

33:51.465 --> 33:59.375
And so if you're not praying a whole lot, if you're praying like once a week or maybe every other day or, you know, that kind of thing, then you're probably not trusting a lot.

34:00.497 --> 34:01.578
So just watch your prayer life.

34:02.179 --> 34:02.940
That's how you watch that.

34:03.941 --> 34:05.783
And then the other thing is how secret are we?

34:05.843 --> 34:07.626
And this is an interesting text.

34:07.666 --> 34:08.106
I have no idea.

34:08.126 --> 34:08.847
I'm going to try to read it.

34:08.867 --> 34:09.428
It's very small.

34:10.049 --> 34:11.070
We'll make it larger next time.

34:12.111 --> 34:17.458
So Jesus says, so that you're giving may be in secret and your father who sees in secret will reward you.

34:17.762 --> 34:23.608
And when you pray, you must not be like the hypocrites, for they love to stand and pray in the synagogues and at the street corners.

34:23.648 --> 34:25.030
Who are the hypocrites he's talking about?

34:25.110 --> 34:25.550
Anybody know?

34:26.671 --> 34:31.336
Yeah, there's religious leaders that we saw in chapter 16 that they may be seen by others.

34:31.737 --> 34:32.438
Yeah, we don't want that.

34:32.998 --> 34:36.362
Truly, I say to you, they have to receive their reward.

34:36.662 --> 34:41.147
And when you pray, go into your room and shut the door and pray to your father who is in secret.

34:41.688 --> 34:44.050
And your father who sees in secret will reward you.

34:44.578 --> 34:52.629
Your fasting may not be seen by others, but by your father who is in secret, and your father who sees in secret rewards.

34:52.669 --> 34:55.113
How good at you at secret spirituality?

34:55.954 --> 34:57.316
We're not parading this kind of thing.

34:57.336 --> 34:58.477
We're not announcing it.

34:59.539 --> 35:01.181
Don't be the hero of your own story.

35:02.123 --> 35:06.629
That's something that I learned in Chicago when I was out there with them, Harvest Bible Chapel.

35:07.670 --> 35:08.972
We were taught that over and over again.

35:09.052 --> 35:10.614
Don't be the hero of your own story.

35:10.635 --> 35:13.138
So if you want to tell a story, I'm not saying be self-deprecating.

35:13.890 --> 35:15.792
Don't beat yourself down, that kind of thing.

35:16.413 --> 35:22.320
But try not to be more secretive about some of those things that that's what he's talking about there.

35:22.380 --> 35:23.822
So there's our application test.

35:24.263 --> 35:25.023
How about we pray together?

35:25.344 --> 35:26.445
Lord, we thank you for your word.

35:27.366 --> 35:31.611
We thank you, Lord, that you're a God who is completely and perfectly in love with us.

35:32.152 --> 35:34.255
And so we just thank you.

35:34.295 --> 35:35.556
We receive all that you have for us.

35:35.596 --> 35:37.418
You are truly a sufficient shepherd.

35:38.420 --> 35:43.666
And so Lord, we know that even though I walked through the valley of the shadow of death, I'll feel no evil.

35:43.906 --> 35:47.551
And so Lord, we pray that you would help us to realize that pride can get in the way of this.

35:48.473 --> 35:49.154
And we don't want that.

35:50.255 --> 35:51.778
And we want to be humble people.

35:52.479 --> 35:53.761
And so we choose humility.

35:54.241 --> 35:57.847
And we pray that you would continuously work this in us as Christians.

35:58.308 --> 36:01.853
And so Lord, we honor you, we give you glory, we praise your name.

36:02.293 --> 36:03.996
It's a tough word, your word on pride.

36:04.076 --> 36:05.038
We don't like to see pride.

36:05.859 --> 36:10.706
God, if there's a blind spot in my life, in our lives, in our church as a whole,

36:11.042 --> 36:12.003
Please reveal it.

36:12.083 --> 36:13.845
We don't want this to be a part of who we are.

36:13.885 --> 36:15.066
No pride.

36:15.747 --> 36:16.287
No pride.

36:17.328 --> 36:25.176
And, Lord, if there's any pride that we're getting right now, just even having conversations with people after first service, people were confessing it, maybe we need to confess it right now.

36:25.716 --> 36:26.938
And I see it in my heart.

36:27.018 --> 36:28.339
Please, Lord, forgive me for pride.

36:28.759 --> 36:29.820
That might be you this morning.

36:30.721 --> 36:35.406
Help us not to have Christianity that we parade our spirituality.

36:35.446 --> 36:36.127
We don't want to do that.

36:36.867 --> 36:39.570
Help us to have more secretive parts of our life.

36:40.002 --> 36:46.752
When it comes to giving, when it comes to fasting, when it comes to all of these other things, Lord, we don't need to be the hero of our own story.

36:47.273 --> 36:48.875
May you be the hero of our story.

36:49.016 --> 36:49.356
That's it.

36:49.516 --> 36:50.177
That's the answer.

36:50.718 --> 36:52.541
May you be the hero of our story.

36:53.242 --> 36:55.305
And so we honor you in Jesus' mighty name.

36:55.605 --> 36:57.048
Let's continue to worship with one more song.

37:02.636 --> 37:06.642
Thanks for listening to the Crossway Christian Church's Middleford Campus Sermon podcast.

37:06.818 --> 37:14.037
If you like to plug into the life of our community or have any questions that we might be able to answer, visit our website at crosswayscc.org to connect with us.

37:14.518 --> 37:15.781
Until next time, we can be with you.

37:16.082 --> 37:17.746
May the Lord bless you and keep you.

